            "content": "{\"message\":\"I will begin the STRIDE\u2010per\u2010element threat enumeration, starting with the two External Entities. Due to the volume of elements, I will split the report into partial deliveries. This first part covers External Entities and their applicable STRIDE threats. Subsequent parts will cover Processes, Data Stores, and Data Flows.\",\"threats\":[{\"id\":1,\"element\":\"Developers / CI/CD\",\"threat_description\":\"An attacker could spoof the identity of an authorized developer or CI/CD pipeline to deploy malicious infrastructure changes.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enforce strong authentication (e.g., Azure AD service principals with MFA), restrict pipeline triggers, and sign all Terraform plans before apply.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:N/A:N\"},{\"id\":2,\"element\":\"Developers / CI/CD\",\"threat_description\":\"Authorized changes provisioned by Terraform cannot be reliably traced back to a unique actor, enabling repudiation of malicious or accidental changes.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable detailed logging and audit trails in Azure Activity Logs, require code reviews, and attach immutable identifiers to pipeline runs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:N\"},{\"id\":3,\"element\":\"End Users / Clients\",\"threat_description\":\"An attacker may spoof client identities (e.g., forge HTTP headers or tokens) to call front\u2010end or back\u2010end Function APIs.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Implement strong authentication/authorization on APIs (e.g., Azure AD, API keys), validate tokens, and enforce origin checks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:N/A:N\"},{\"id\":4,\"element\":\"End Users / Clients\",\"threat_description\":\"Clients may deny having sent certain requests (e.g., malicious or abusive API calls) due to lack of proper request logging.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Log all incoming requests with timestamps, source IPs, and authentication context in a tamper\u2010evident store.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:N\"}],\"is_final\":false}"
